The Dow Jones Industrial Average is flat Monday morning with shares of Walgreens Boots and Merck leading the way for the price-weighted average. The Dow DJIA, -0.36% is trading at 25,871, unchanged from yesterday's close. Walgreens Boots's shares have declined $0.94, or 2.1%, while those of Merck are off $1.34, or 1.7%, combining for a roughly 16-point drag on the Dow. Other components contributing significantly include Caterpillar CAT, +0.36%, Boeing BA, -0.85%, and Pfizer PFE, -0.05%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the benchmark equates to a 6.86-point swing.

